name: Supporters in
Testimonial: I have listened from the first episode. I have turned on coworkers and my son and daughter to Ear Hustle. We all love the show. - Veronica B. (Birmingham, AL), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: Thank you for this amazing show! It's on my must listen to list. - James B. (Chandler, AZ), This Day supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: Beautifully crafted art pieces of hope, emotion, kindness, differences. Thank you for softening my heart each episode. - Arthur M. (Kensington, CA), The Memory Palace supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: Love, love, LOVED the serial show Appearances! Thank you for such a beautiful, thoughtful, funny, and touching experience. - Melina B. (Englewood, CO), PRX supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: I love your show. It’s truly an important way to shine a light on all aspects of the “justice” system in America. - Laura M. (Stratford, CT), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: THANK YOU! For covering stories that aren’t covered anywhere else. And for the variety of your stories-political, cultural, sports, arts news. I feel like I must listen every night to be a citizen of The World. You all do a fabulous, necessary job! - Cathleen O. (Washington, DC), The World supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: Love you folks so much! Thank you for your service and dedication. - Victoria A. (St. Petersburg, FL), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: Please keep up the balanced and extensive coverage of world news. I listen to you daily ... You are one of the few news sources that I trust. - Vijaya S. (Atlanta, GA), The World supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: I've been listening to your stellar program for a number of years. So grateful for your insights and potent storytelling. Your team helps us understand the facets of our world through the lens of the environment, politics, art, and culture. It's about connection -- so much intelligence and wit, generosity and heart that moves through each broadcast. Public radio/media is a powerful community resource, and this public space is so enriched with your presence. Thank you for providing us these connections across this beautiful planet of ours. You are so deeply appreciated! - Jessica E. (Makawao, HI), The World supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: The work you do is important, we need more empathy in the world. - Emma P. (Altoona, IA), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: The work you do is vitally important. As a long time listener, I can honestly say the stories you share have made me a better person. - Heide H. (Boise, ID), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: The work you do is vitally important. As a long time listener, I can honestly say the stories you share have made me a better person. - Heide H. (Boise, ID), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: I’ve listened to every episode and love the show. Thanks for your amazing storytelling. I wonder if you might do a tour of college towns one day? Places like Bloomington, IN… - Jennifer B. (Bloomington, IN), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: I really enjoy listening to your podcast every evening. Keep up the good work. You give a perspective that I cannot find elsewhere. - Dorothy M. (Amherst, MA), The World supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: "Nate, just discovering your show and I'm in love. Your voice, your storytelling skills, your timing. It's all fantastic. Thank you so much. - Thomas O. (Bethesda, MD), The Memory Palace supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: Thank you for this masterpiece of a podcast. Listening to how humans learn to adapt to their environment, regardless the circumstances, and hearing how people evolve and grow through their prison experience has been incredibly eye-opening. It is so easy to judge someone by their crime, and ignore their humanity, but Ear Hustle gives a platform for folks to express the emotional, creative, and true selves, somewhat divorced from the action(s) giving rise to their imprisonment. Thank you for all your hard work and the respect and empathy you display with each show. - Amy O. (South Portland, ME), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: I wish I could give more because you have opened my eyes and deepened my understanding about so many things. What you are doing is SO important! I thank each and every one of you, both inside and outside. - Renee C. (Richmond, MI), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: I listen every day -- The World is the best source of international news with excellent reporting and stories behind the headlines that I often relate to others. - Paula D. (Minneapolis, MN), The World supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: ...it is essential to have reporters on the ground giving us an unbiased look at the important stories from every region of our planet. - Anonymous (Pass Christian, MS) The World supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: Listening to Ear Hustle has opened my eyes in so many ways! It has deepened my empathy for the students I serve, many of which come from broken homes, often with incarcerated parents. It has deepened my understanding of the many reasons for recidivism, and the many creative ways we can all work together to reduce it. It has given me a deeper passion for justice, and has enabled me to become more active in my local government to demand said justice for more people than are currently being served. Ear Hustle has been a revelation. -- Hilary L., Polson, MT | Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: Keep up the solid journalism work you do and provide! Anonymous (Charlotte, NC), PRX supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: I am grateful for EarHustle. You have broadened my understanding and deepened my compassion. - Donna G. (Lincoln, NE), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: I have been listening since the beginning and love Ear Hustle. - Leaf S. (Hancock, NH), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in
Testimonial: Please keep doing what you are doing. In a time when people want to force others to be no more than caricatures of a whole group, you show the humanity and individuality of people who otherwise are marginalized. Thank you. - Douglas V. (Rahway, NJ), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Supporters in

name: KALW:
